 "coaching": {
  "headline": "A 23-minute win you should not over-read: you were draft-behind in two of three solo lanes and got bailed out by objective control and one outlier carry game.",
  "team": "Scoreline says stomp (VP +19, deaths in the single digits across the team), but the sim disagrees with the draft: Argus into Iggy & Scorch and Grux into Bayle both read 'theirs all game' on kill-window — you lost the solo-lane draft on paper. What actually won the game was the bottom/jungle side and objectives: 3 objective kills to 1 and roughly 3x their objective damage (32.7k vs 10.9k). That is the repeatable lesson — you choke objectives well. The non-repeatable part is Sparrow posting a 234 performance score, +124 over his OWN average on the hero; you cannot draft assuming that every game. Comp was 3 physical / 2 magical into their 4 physical, you had a real frontline (Grux) and they ran zero healers, so itemization pressure was low — which is why nobody got punished for thin defensive buys this game.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "94c5268d-0a37-4b78-850c-a1a83c7ea741": "Carried it — 7/0/5, 234 performance, +124 over your hero average. Blunt truth: this is an outlier, not your baseline, so don't let it validate the build. You went Sky Splitter/crit; our sim's higher-floor line on Sparrow is on-hit/lethality (Viper → Deathstalker → Vanquisher). Crit worked because you were ahead and the game ended at 23 — into a longer game vs armor stacking, the on-hit line holds up better. Keep the aggression, test the on-hit core next time you're even.",
   "528d6c33-2ca6-41eb-8dc0-be9b942503f5": "5/0/4, never died, 170 performance (+54 over your 6-game average — you're still learning this hero and it didn't show). You opened correctly: Combustion + Azure Core is the field mana line and the sim agrees. After that you drifted to Diffusal Cane / Potent Staff / Soulbearer instead of the haste/uptime core (Entropy, Wraith Leggings, Timewarp). Fine in a 23-minute game; in a 35-minute one that's lost ability uptime in exactly the fights that decide it. You were draft-unfavored into Iggy & Scorch all game — respect that lane in the early game next time, you got away with it here.",
   "62dc40d1-e531-4777-abd6-f44217bdb3bb": "9/2/2, 137 performance, +23 over a 22-game comfort pick — your best role. Sim flags no armor into a 4-physical enemy comp; on a dueling jungler that's a deliberate glass tradeoff and it paid (9 kills), but it's the line between this game and feeding when you're not ahead. You also drifted off the Spear of Desolation / Viper core into Basilisk/Salvation — situationally fine, just know it's off the optimal damage line.",
   "ddc5a299-6a24-40ec-9834-cbba2de2807b": "3/3/5, 123 performance, +25 over a 455-game mastery pick. You were the frontline and the draft put you behind into Bayle (sim: their lane early). 3 deaths in a 23-minute win is the one number to clean up — you were even-to-behind, so dying three times is tempo you handed back. No armor into 4 physical on an offlane bruiser is the itemization note; you can afford one defensive item without losing your threat.",
   "0585f41a-4c01-423a-a063-cb38728029ce": "0/1/7, 122 performance on a 161-game pile of reps. Textbook supportive line — one death, seven assists, and you got the Dynamo aura down. Missing the Stonewall/defensive layer the sim wants on you into a heavy-physical enemy, but with no enemy healers and a frontline already up, low-impact this game. Clean game; nothing to fix, more to add."
  },
  "whatShiftedIt": "Nothing needed to shift it — you won. The honest takeaway is what would have made it FRAGILE: lose Sparrow's outlier game and you're a team that drafted two losing solo lanes and itemized thin on defense into a physical comp. Bank the objective control (that's the repeatable edge), respect the mid/offlane matchups in the draft, and let the optimizer's build lines carry the long games where an outlier performance can't bail you out."
 }
}